    "Like, especially if you want to, if you want to use turnkey tools, there's always going to be a finding that tools, especially those that can cause access control issues, business logic issues, or deeper issues that pen testing might find, aren't always that good.",
    "You can tune it to work quickly in a DevOps environment, and perhaps only one in five people will find that manual operations may miss issues.",
    "The dark side of DevOps is that we still need people.",
    "We can't just automate everything.",
    "I think we still need people who are involved in deep vetting to really provide a deeper level of security assurance if you need it."
